UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2106
1 of all money wagered on historical horse races at the track for
2 harness racing shall be distributed in the exact amounts based
3 upon contracts between the parties that have been filed with the
4 corporation, but at least one-half (1/2) of the funds shall be
5 deposited into the Kentucky standardbred development fund
6 established in KRS 230.770 until a total of twenty million dollars
7 ($20,000,000) has been deposited into the Kentucky standardbred
8 development fund during a fiscal year from this subparagraph, at
9 which point the amount deposited in this subdivision shall
10 decrease to four-tenths of one percent (0.4%) of all money
11 wagered for the remainder of the fiscal year. The corporation shall
12 provide the department all information necessary from the
13 contracts in order for the funds in this subparagraph to be
14 distributed;
15 3. a. An amount equal to one percent (1%) of all money wagered on
16 live races and historical horse races at the track for paint horse,
17 Appaloosa, and Arabian horse racing shall be deposited in the
18 Kentucky paint horse, Appaloosa, and Arabian development fund
19 established by KRS 230.445; and
20 b. An amount equal to one percent (1%) of all money wagered on
21 live races and historical horse races at the track for quarter horse
22 racing shall be deposited in the Kentucky quarter horse
23 development fund established by KRS 230.405;
24 4. An amount equal to two-tenths of one percent (0.2%) of all money
25 wagered on live races and historical horse races at the track shall be paid
26 out in equal amounts as follows:
27 a. To the equine industry program trust and revolving fund
Page 3 of 15
XXXX 2/18/2026 1:46 PM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2106
1 established by KRS 230.550 to support the Equine Industry
2 Program at the University of Louisville, except that the amount
3 deposited from money wagered on historical horse races in any
4 fiscal year shall not exceed eight hundred fifty thousand dollars
5 ($850,000);
6 b. To the University of Kentucky for equine industry programs at the
7 university, except that the amount paid from money wagered on
8 historical horse races in any fiscal year shall not exceed four
9 hundred thousand dollars ($400,000);
10 c. To the Bluegrass Community and Technical College for the
11 provision of equine industry programs by the system, except that
12 the amount paid from money wagered on historical horse races in
13 any fiscal year shall not exceed two hundred fifty thousand dollars
14 ($250,000);
15 d. Amounts remaining from money wagered on historical horse races
16 in a fiscal year after payments are made in accordance with
17 subdivisions a., b., and c. of this subparagraph shall be distributed
18 in equal amounts to:
19 i. The Kentucky Horse Racing and Gaming Corporation for the
20 benefit of Thoroughbred, standardbred, and American
21 quarter horse aftercare facilities in Kentucky, in an amount
22 not to exceed two hundred fifty thousand dollars ($250,000).
23 The Kentucky Horse Racing and Gaming Corporation shall
24 serve as the administrative agent for these funds, and shall
25 distribute them annually to organizations engaged in the
26 accreditation and monitoring of aftercare facilities. Any
27 funds distributed under this subpart by the Kentucky Horse
Page 4 of 15
