1 Racing and Gaming Corporation shall be awarded to
2 aftercare facilities based in Kentucky only after the facilities
3 have achieved and maintained levels of service and operation
4 that resulted in national accreditation; and
5 ii. The Kentucky equine management internship program for
6 equine management training, in an amount not to exceed two
7 hundred fifty thousand dollars ($250,000); and
8 e. Any amounts remaining from money wagered on historical horse
9 races in a fiscal year after payments are made in accordance with
10 subdivisions a., b., c., and d. of this subparagraph shall be paid to
11 the general fund;
12 5. a. An amount equal to one-tenth of one percent (0.1%) of all money
13 wagered on live races and historical horse races at the track shall
14 be deposited in a trust and revolving fund to be used for the
15 construction, expansion, or renovation of facilities or the purchase
16 of equipment for equine programs at state universities and the
17 Bluegrass Community and Technical College, except that the
18 amount deposited from money wagered on historical horse races in
19 any fiscal year shall not exceed three hundred twenty thousand
20 dollars ($320,000).
21 b. These funds shall not be used for salaries or for operating funds
22 for teaching, research, or administration. Funds allocated under
23 this subparagraph shall not replace other funds for capital purposes
24 or operation of equine programs at state universities and the
25 Bluegrass Community and Technical College.
26 c. The Kentucky Council on Postsecondary Education shall serve as
27 the administrative agent for these funds, and shall establish an
Page 5 of 15
