6 this subsection during the fiscal year.
7 (c) A noncontiguous track facility approved by the corporation on or after
8 January 1, 1999, shall be exempt from the tax imposed under this subsection,
9 if the facility is established and operated by a licensed track which has a total
10 annual handle on live racing of two hundred fifty thousand dollars ($250,000)
11 or less. The amount of money exempted under this paragraph shall be retained
12 by the noncontiguous track facility, KRS 230.3771 and 230.378
13 notwithstanding.
14 (d) Money shall be deducted from the tax paid under paragraphs (a) and (b) of
15 this subsection as follows:
16 1. An amount equal to one percent (1%) of the amount wagered shall be
17 deposited as follows:
18 a. In the Thoroughbred development fund established in KRS
19 230.400 if the host track is conducting a Thoroughbred race
