1 calculating the daily average live handle for purposes of subsection (1) of this
2 section.
3 (4) If a host track in this state is the location for the conduct of an international harness
4 racing event spanning multiple days that distributes at least five million dollars
5 ($5,000,000) in purses and awards, the Tourism, Arts and Heritage Cabinet shall be
6 granted a race title sponsorship and promotional package at the international
7 harness racing event with all usual and customary benefits assigned to promote
8 Kentucky tourism. The Tourism, Arts and Heritage Cabinet shall not be charged
9 any fees for the promotional package.
10 (5) The taxes imposed by this section shall be paid, collected, and administered as
