12 SECTION 2. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 230 IS CREATED TO
13 READ AS FOLLOWS:
14 (1) The pari-mutuel racing local government support fund in the State Treasury is
15 hereby created and shall be:
16 (a) A trust and agency account administered by the Department for Local
17 Government in accordance with this section; and
18 (b) Disbursed by the State Treasurer upon the warrant of the commissioner of
19 the Department for Local Government.
20 (2) This fund shall consist of moneys received in accordance with the distribution
21 formula established in Section 1 of this Act.
22 (3) Notwithstanding KRS 45.229, moneys remaining in the account at the close of
23 the fiscal year shall not lapse but shall carry forward into the succeeding fiscal
24 year.
25 (4) Moneys in the fund shall be used to support local governments where live and
26 historical horse racing facilities are located and as specified in subsections (5)
27 and (6) of this section.
Page 9 of 15
XXXX 2/18/2026 1:46 PM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2106
1 (5) The Department for Local Government shall promulgate administrative
2 regulations in accordance with KRS Chapter 13A that direct how local
3 governments may use moneys from this fund to address the social costs of
4 problem gambling, including but not limited to:
5 (a) Law enforcement retention;
6 (b) Homelessness;
7 (c) Affordable housing; and
8 (d) The policing, regulation, and administration of the facilities where live and
9 historical horse racing facilities are located.
10 (6) (a) The moneys in the fund shall be disbursed, at least quarterly, to counties
11 containing tracks or facilities that are paying the excise tax that ultimately
12 is deposited into the fund.
13 (b) The Department for Local Government shall:
14 1. Determine the amount of excise tax generated and paid by each track
15 or facility;
16 2. Determine the portion of the moneys in the fund related to that excise
17 tax; and
18 3. Distribute the tax to the appropriate county.
19 (7) The Department for Local Government shall promulgate administrative
20 regulations in accordance with KRS Chapter 13A related to:
21 (a) The requirements for qualification for distribution of the moneys from this
22 fund to local governments, which shall include:
23 1. Application and reporting requirements for local governments;
24 2. A list of eligible expenses by the local governments; and
25 3. Accountability criteria for local governments to receive moneys; and
26 (b) Distributions to the local governments, which shall include guidelines for
27 the allocation of moneys for local governments which include both cities
Page 10 of 15
